  "texts": [
    "First, comparing efficacy of surprisals and the existing cohesion indices can provide enhanced objectivity and consistency in assessing degree expressions.",
    "LLMs can analyze degree expressions by evaluating the statistical predictability of words and structures within these expressions.",
    "TAACO provides indices that measure various aspects of textual cohesion, including how effectively degree expressions and comparatives are made and linked in a text.",
    "These indices can reflect the clarity and coherence of degree expressions, essential for evaluating L2 learners' proficiency in using such structures.",
    "Comparing these two approaches allows us to explore the extent to which statistical language predictability (surprisal) aligns with or complements classic cohesion measures."
  ],
